{
  "answer": "The mermaid-cli package provides a Node.js API for rendering diagrams locally and does not require authentication [1][2][3]. Authentication methods mentioned in related Mermaid documentation, such as OAuth2 or token-based Authorization headers, apply only to the separate Mermaid Chart API or specific MCP server integrations, not to the mermaid-cli command-line tool or its programmatic Node.js API [4][5][6]. You can use the mermaid-cli Node.js API by importing and executing the run function as shown below [1][2].\n\n```js\nimport { run } from \"@mermaid-js/mermaid-cli\";\n\nawait run(\"input.mmd\", \"output.svg\");\n```",
